events.title: Indoor Cycling
events.description: Increase your cardio and strength with our indoor cycling class. Get your heart pumping with a series of sprints, hills, and drills to build endurance, burn calories and relieve stress. This multi-level class will motivate you through music and moves that allow you to set the intensity of your workout and cruise at your own pace.

events.title: Women's Only: Strength 101
events.description: Have you hit a plateau or feel like you’re not getting any stronger? Our expert trainers will guide you through the steps to achieve your strength goals with a dynamic and strength targeted workouts. We will use a variety of exercises and state of the art equipment in our Strength and Conditioning Center.  Challenge yourself in a supportive and motivating environment and achieve your fitness goals with our invigorating strength class.  No matter your fitness level, this is a perfect class to learn the proper technique, fine tune your strength training program, or take it to the next level as an experienced lifter.

events.title: Hatha Yoga
events.description: This gentle class begins with a guided meditation, introduces yoga postures to stretch and strengthen the body, and teaches relaxation practices to reduce stress and calm the mind. Taught in a supportive environment, this 45-minute class is ideal for beginners, but all levels are welcome. Yoga mats are provided.

events.title: Flow Yoga
events.description: Energize your day with our Flow Yoga class. Move seamlessly through poses synchronizing the breath to movement while elevating your heart rate for this total body mindful workout.

events.title: Pilates
events.description: Achieve a balanced and toned body with the ultimate core fitness workout!  Incorporate Pilate’s postures with traditional core exercises to help improve posture, strength, and range of motion.  Rejuvenate your workout with a focus on your breathing and find those deep core muscles in the abdomen and that surround the spine.  All fitness levels welcome.

events.title: Intermediate Boxing
events.description: Build upon the foundations of the jab and cross learned in our Beginner Boxing class. This class introduces the hook, uppercut, and more complex sequences focused on building rhythm. Some boxing experience is recommended if participants have not yet attended our other boxing classes. *Hand wraps, gloves and non-slip shoes are recommended!

events.description: This class offers a fusion experience of traditional high intensity indoor cycling with implementation of core exercises to fire up your whole body! Get registered today to improve your cardiovascular and core endurance, and strength

An inclusive, fun, and supportive environment that will teach you effective exercises and challenge you to reach your goals.

Rainbow Rythm is not just about getting fit; it’s about feeling your best self and connecting with others who share a commitment to a healthy lifestyle.

Our aquatic instructors will meet you at your current swimming level and work with you to develop and enhance your skills. Whether you’re conquering floats and glides or beginning to learn your strokes, come by, say hi, and let us help you meet your swimming goals!

events.title: Black Learn to Swim
events.description: Black Learn to Swim is an introductory program for Black identified students designed to focus on water safety and building your confidence in an aquatic environment - all skill levels are welcome! Our aquatic instructors will meet you at your current swimming level and work with you to develop and enhance your skills. Whether you’re conquering floats and glides or beginning to learn your strokes, come by, say hi, and let us help you meet your swimming goals! We offer a Soul Cap and body cream during this swim.

events.title: Cycle Core
events.description: This class offers a fusion experience of traditional high intensity indoor cycling with implementation of core exercises to fire up your whole body! Get registered today to improve your cardiovascular and core endurance, and strength.

events.title: Women on Weights
events.description: A class that caters to women's needs and wants! Providing a safe space to get energized while building up strength and muscle. Push yourself and raise your limits with our women focused circuit training using a mix of cardio and weights. An inclusive, fun, and supportive environment that will teach you effective exercises and challenge you to reach your goals.

events.title: Women's Only: Beginner Boxing
events.description: Learn how to pack a punch in this technical workshop designed to teach beginners the basics of boxing. This session provides instructions on boxing stance, footwork, and fundamental mechanics of the jab, cross, hook and uppercut. Join this fun session to stay in shape and build your confidence!This class is open to female identifying members.

events.title: Pride Badminton and Volleyball
events.description: Pride Sports offers a unique drop-in Sports experience in an inclusive setting for the 2SLGTBQ+ community and allies. Join us for fun and social sports atmosphere that celebrate diversity and foster community. Tailored for 2SLGTBQ+ students, Pride Sports will provide a variety of sport offerings and have support from our Sport Inclusion Ambassador to ensure you have the equipment you need and provide support for a fun, inclusive and positive session. You don’t need to be a sport expert to come and join the fun!

events.title: BIPOC Badminton and Volleyball
events.description: BIPOC Sport Drop-in is a fun and social drop-in sports time that will provide further offerings for individuals within the BIPOC (Black, Indigenous, and People of Color) community. This dedicated time slot for various drop-in sports that will offer a safe and inclusive space to come together and prioritize their health and well-being. Build your sport skills in a fun and inclusive environment and our Sport Inclusion Ambassador will ensure you have the equipment and support you need to have a fun and positive session. You don’t need to be a sport expert to come and join the fun!

events.title: Registered Lessons
events.description: We are proud to offer swimming lessons at UTM for all levels and a variety of age groups. Please see our website for full details and information.

events.title: Intro to Coached Swim
events.description: The UTM Intro to Coached Swim program is for individuals seeking a gym alternative for fitness, those training for triathlons, and competitive swimming training who might have limited coached environment experience. The program is designed to enhance competitive swimming abilities, stroke techniques, and personal fitness. This program will introduce the structure of a coached swim and provide a challenging workout for those new to the coached environment. events.title: UTM Walks

events.title: Rainbow Rhythm
events.description: Rainbow Rhythm is a lively aerobics class that centers around the 2SLGBTQ+ community! This vibrant program combines high-energy movement with an inclusive atmosphere that welcomes individuals of all fitness levels. Participants are encouraged to express themselves through dance and movement in a supportive environment that fosters self-acceptance and joy. Rainbow Rythm is not just about getting fit; it’s about feeling your best self and connecting with others who share a commitment to a healthy lifestyle.

announcements.title: The SCC will be closed March 2 to March 17
announcements.body:
Please note that the Strength and Conditioning Centre will be closed from Sunday, March 2 - Monday, March 17 due to scheduled space upgrades.
A number of classes have been relocated or cancelled due to scheduled work.
Please visit our website for the most up to date schedule here:  [Schedule | Recreation, Athletics & Wellness](https://www.utm.utoronto.ca/athletics/schedule?program_id=4 "https://www.utm.utoronto.ca/athletics/schedule?program_id=4")
We appreciate your patience and understanding as we revamp our spaces!
